Durban - A Richard's Bay man who was initially charged with bomb threat has been now charged with assault by threat. According to KZN police spokesperson, a 36-year-old man was arrested on Tuesday after he allegedly went to a building in Richard's Bay where he threatened to kill everyone with a bomb. "Police were called and evacuated the place. A search was conducted and no suspicious parcel found." Zwane said the suspect was arrested and charged for bomb threat. However, when the man appeared on Thursday in the Richard's Bay Magistrate's Court he was charged with assault by threat. According to NPA spokesperson Natasha Kara-Ramkisson the accused Yudesh Partab, 36, made his first appearance and was remanded in police custody. "The matter was adjourned to January 30 for verification of information." When asked what the charge meant Kara explained that the complainant feels they are in danger / or when the fear of danger is apprehended. Daily News